<BODY BACKGROUND="arcback2.gif">
<P>
<CENTER><I><B><FONT SIZE=7 FACE="Arial">ABOUT  ....</FONT><FONT SIZE=5 FACE="Arial">
 INSURANCE<BR>
</FONT></B></I></CENTER>
<P>
<I><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">No matter<I><B> what</B> kind of
member you are - self advocate, parent, family, staff, service
provider, board, executive director, chapter, etc., you should
know that The Arc is thinking about your insurance needs and how
to meet them in the most available, inclusive and affordable ways
possible. <BR>
</I></FONT></I>
<P>
<I><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">The Arc is actively engaged in designing
innovative life, health, property, liability and other individual
and group insurance programs that will benefit people with mental
retardation and their families as well as state and local chapters,
by offering a sound choice for managing risks.  Listed below are
the current insurance programs of The Arc. <BR>
</FONT></I>
<P>
<U><B><FONT FACE="Arial">INSURANCE POLICIES PROVIDED AT NO CHARGE
TO CHAPTERS OF THE ARC</FONT></B></U>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">The Arc Fidelity Bond Coverage: 
</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">Provides protection for loss
due to dishonest act by officers, volunteers or employees. The
policy has a $100,000 limit (subject to a $7,500 deductible).
<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<U><B><FONT FACE="Arial">POLICIES AVAILABLE TO CHAPTERS OF THE
ARC AT DISCOUNT RATES</FONT></B></U>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">The Arc Directors and Officers Liability
Coverage</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">: </FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">Blanket Policy:  </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">Provides
protection for the chapter's directors, officers, trustees, committee
members, executive director and all employees for losses they
become legally obligated to pay by reason of a wrongful act or
alleged wrongful act, including legal costs. It is written with
a limit of $1,000,000 per chapter with a $5,000,000 national aggregate.</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">Coverage with No National Aggregate:
 </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">Provides same coverage as
the Blanket Policy, except is written with limits of $500,000,
$1,000,000 or $2,000,000 with individual chapter aggregates. 
For additional information and application forms, please contact:</FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><B><FONT FACE="Arial">PAUL H GREENBERG AGENCY 1-800-726-0752
<BR>
</FONT></B></CENTER>
<P>
<U><B><FONT FACE="Arial">INSURANCE POLICIES FOR WHICH MEMBERS
OF THE ARC MAY QUALIFY</FONT></B></U>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">The Arc Major Medical Insurance Plan
for Persons with Mental Retardation:  </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">Major
Medical Health Insurance for people with mental retardation between
the ages of 10 and 65 who are members or offspring of members.
Members without disabilities, their spouse, dependent children
up to age 19 (age 23 if a full-time student) and key employees
(working at least 30 hours per week) and their spouses may also
apply for this coverage. The plan offers a comprehensive option
as well as a lower cost economy option.  Each option has three
different deductibles offering coverage up to 1,000,000 for you,
your family and employees.  <B>(Policies not available in all
states.)</B>  To obtain information about this policy please contact:
<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">The Arc Security Life Insurance Plan
for Persons with Mental Retardation:  </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">Provides
protection up to $42,000 in increments of $3,000, at competitive
rates, for persons with mental retardation from age 2 to 60, renewable
to age 80. The minimum coverage of $3,000 is guaranteed for long-standing
members of The Arc. <BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">The Arc Security Life Insurance Plan
for Families and Friends:  </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">Provides
protection up to $300,000 for members of The Arc or their spouses.
Proof of insurability required.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">The Arc In-Hospital Dollars:  </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">Provides
up to $200 per day coverage when confined in a hospital regardless
of other plans in effect. Guaranteed to members of The Arc, subject
to a limitation on pre-existing conditions.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">The Arc Medicare Supplement:  </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">Provides
supplemental insurance coverage for persons utilizing Medicare.
Pays costs above Medicare coverage, subject to limitations. Guaranteed
to members of The Arc. For additional information and application
forms for the above policies, please contact:<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><B><FONT FACE="Arial">ALBERT H. WOHLERS &amp; COMPANY
1-800-323-2106</FONT></B></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><B><FONT FACE="CG Times"><a href="mailto:info@ahw.com">Email use:  For Brochures- info@ahw.com </a> <br>
<a href="mailto:cusv@ahw.com">For information/service: cusv@ahw.com</a><br>
</FONT></B></CENTER>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Arial">For additional information contact:<br>
 Member, Chapter &amp; Communication Services, National Headquarters<br>
500 E. Border, Suite 300, Arlington, TX 76010 <br>
(817) 261-6003 Fax  (817) 277-3491 TDD   (817) 277-0553 Toll
Free 1-800-433-5255<br>  Email: thearc@metronet.com </FONT><FONT SIZE=1 FACE="Arial"><BR>
