<title>Community-Care Rap</title>
</head>
<body background="../images/backgrounds/sandston.gif">
<h1 align=center><img src="../images/icons/eyes.gif"></h1>
<h2 align=center>Community Care Rap</h2>
<h4 align=center>Now hey there people
won't you lend me your ear?<br>
I've a story to tell
and I'm telling it here.<br>
Community Care is the
latest craze,<br>
How to access the system?
it's just a maze.<br>
You're a User or Carer,
so what could be fairer<br>
than not to let you choose,
and ignore your views?<br>
The fat controllers at the top,<br>
they don't give a fig
they don't give a jot.<br>
So long as their empire
is big and strong,<br>
they will do as they like
and see no wrong.<br>

Community Care
it's here to stay,<br>
Empowerment is
the word of the day,<br>
in reality, they wish it
would all go away.<br>
If oonly they'd listen
to you and me<br>
we'd make them realise,
we'd make them see<br>
we're the experts when
it comes to our need,<br>
we're fair and practical
and not full of greed.<br>
Users and Carers have
the skill and the will<br>
to make them listen and
listen they will.<br>
If we work together
to pave the way<br>
you'd have yours and
we'd have our say.<br>
But from experience
I have to say<br>
they're not listening
here, they're not
listening there.<br>
I ask you people are
they listening anywhere?<br>
The development of
power is a real tough
thing,<br> when we are the
puppets and they pull
the string.<br>
The message from us
is strong and clear,<br>
it's time the authorities
played it fair,<br>
and worked with users 
and carers<br> for the good
of Community Care.<br>
So don't marginalise,
don't marginalise,<br>
demoralize or
patronize,<br>
because we outnumber
you<br> and are streetwise
too.<br>
So let's work together
as from today,<br>
Cos Community Care
is here to stay.<p>
Elaine Driver <a href="/Making_Space/">(Making Space)</a>

</h4>
<p>
<h1 align=center><img src="../images/icons/eyes.gif"></h1>
<h3 align=center>Give all you can - Take only what you need<br>
People come First!</h3>
<h5 align=center><a href="index.html"><img src="../images/icons/back.gif" alt="Back"></a></h5>


