<title>Signpost</title>
</head>
<body  bgcolor=#ffffff >
<h4 align=center><img src=../images/logos/sign2.gif alt=Signpost for Carers></h4><blockquote>
<h3 align=center>Pointing you in the right direction and supporting you along the way</h3>
<b>Signpost Stockport</b> is an independant charity which provides free confidential information for Carers in Stockport of whatever age, who are looking after relatives, or friends who are ill, disabled or frail and who cannot manage at home without their help.
<p>
As a Carer you may not always be aware of where to go for help or where to go if you need to talk to someone who understands the problems you are facing.
<p>
<b>Signpost</b> can offer you advice as to what services are available to support you in your Caring role. We can send you with the <b>'Find Out'</b> guide, a free reference to services available in Stockport. We can also send you our free quarterly newsletter <b>'Carelink'</b> which focuses on issues of particular interest to Carers.
<p>
<b>Signpost</b> also has a Young Carers project, providing information and support to children and young adults
<p>
<b>You can contact us for help with:</b>
<ul>
<li>Emotional Support
<li>Equipment and Adaptions
<li>Holidays and Leisure
<li>Housing and Accommodation
<li>Health Care
<li>Local carers Groups
<li>Practical Help
<li>Residential Care
<li>Respite Care
<li>Transport - Mobility
<li>Welfare Benefits and Grants
</ul>
<p>
<b>The organisation</b>
<ul>
<li>has a free guide to sources of help for Carers
<li>has a free quarterly newsletter for Carers and professionals who work with them
<li>has an extensive range of information material specifically for Carers
<li>has a confidential telephone helpline (24 hour answerphone available)
<li>provides expertise for Carers as one of six local Charities operating the Info Line Community Information
Service, with minicom and 24 hour answering machine
<ul>
<li><b><li>Info Line telephone number :- 0161-456-0096</b>
</ul>
<li>is involved in raising public awareness of the needs of Carers and actively seeks out Carers who may not appreciate that they are Carers
<li>encourages individual Carers to make their views and needs known
<li>works as part of multi-agency groups with representatives from the statutory, voluntary and independant sectors as approriate, to aid the planning and development of services to support Carers in Stockport
<li>has a Young Carers Project
</ul>
<hr>
