<body  bgcolor=#ffffff >
<h4 align=center><img src=../images/logos/sdg1.gif alt=Stockport Disability Group></h4><br><br><blockquote>
<b>Stockport Disability Group</b> offers a free and confidential informmation and advice service to disabled people, families and carers.
<p>

We can give information on a wide range of subjects incuding <b>Access and Planning, Holidays, Equipment, Aids and Adaptions, Transport, Mobility and Leisure Activities</b> and can also tell you about other organisations which can give practical and other help.

<p>

We can lend a sympathetic ear when you feel you have explored all the other options and can help you find your way to the services you need.

<p>

Stockport Disability Group is working towards ensuring equality of opportunity for disabled people and the recognition by society that what improves life for disabled people would improve life for everybody.

<p>

Our quarterly newsletter 'Viewpoint' is full of interesting and vital information for disabled people. We publish a 'Find Out' guide to services in Stockport which is available free to disabled people and carers.

<p>

We can provide courses in disablity awareness training especially tailored to the needs of your organisation. 

<p>

We have a subsidised, adapted, accessible holiday caravan at Prestatyn, North Wales. Bookings are taken from the beginning of January each year. Prices available on request.

<p>

<b>connect plus</b> is dedicated to leisure activities and can provide disabled adults in Stockport with a Leisure Companion to accomany them during their leisure time and the activity of their choice.

<p>

<h4 align=center>connect plus can be reached on: 0161-474-0048<p>Stockport Disability Group confidential info line: 0161-480-7248</h4>

