Subject: Litigation
<p>
I live in Tasmania and have had CFS (Australian for ME) since 1994.  I 
don't need diagnostic help or therapy advice as the team at Newcastle 
[New South Wales] University is a world leader in ME/CFS research.
<p>
What would help me, please, would be any data on successful (or not!) 
litigation [British, Irish, European, Canadian, US, etc.] involving 
claims against any employer(s) for negligence in inducing MECFS in 
employee(s) either by 
1) operating a poorly constructed or incompetently maintained (i.e.Sick) 
Building,  (i.e.the toxic route to ME/CFS,) or by
2) forcing an employee to perform a new, huge and sustained overload of 
work leading to collapse and ME/CFS (i.e. the stress route to ME/CFS).
<p>
Thanks in advance to any patient, carer, survivor, doctor or lawyer with 
knowledge of such cases or of cases where other, non-ME types of injury 
or long-term illness arose in similar circumstances.
<p>
Does anyone know of a way of accessing relevant on-line UK or Irish 
Court Reports? 
<p>
Tom McGlynn <a href="mailto:tmcglynn@postoffice.newnham.utas.edu.au">  tmcglynn@postoffice.newnham.utas.edu.au</a>

