<h2 align=center><IMG SRC ="../images/logos/banner.gif"></h2>
<p>
<h2 align=center><IMG SRC = "../images/icons/eyes.gif"></h2>
<p>

<p>
<h2 align=center><i>What is CFIDS/ME?</i></h2>
<br>
<blockquote>
What a brilliant question! CFIDS and ME are the two common international abreviations for the same serious and complex illness
that affects many different body systems. CFIDS stands for Chronic Fatigue and Immune Dysfunction Syndrome, and ME stands for Myalgic Encephalomyelitis. The specific cause has not yet been well understood.  It is characterized by incapacitating fatigue (experienced as profound exhaustion and extemely poor stamina), neurological problems, and numerous other symptoms. It can be seriously debilitating and last for many years. Because CFIDS/ME is often unrecognized and can resemble other disorders, it is frequently misdiagnosed. <p>

<p>

Persons with CFIDS (PWCs) experience numerous symptoms which tend to  vary on an individual basis and flucuate in severity. Specific
symptoms may come and go, further complicating treatment and the ability to cope with the illness. Most symptoms are not visible to
others, which makes it difficult for them to understand how much discomfort PWCs experience. <p>
</blockquote>
<br>

<h2 align=center><IMG SRC = "../images/icons/eyes.gif"></h2>

<p>

<h2 align=center><i>Referral Information</i></h2><p>

<br>
<blockquote>
If you or someone you know has an undiagnosed illness that has lasted for several months or has CFIDS/ME and needs a doctor or attorney, email us with the details including name, location, and type of assistance required.  We will do our best to assist you in finding a solution or information. Email us at: <A HREF=mailto:schweit2@ix.netcom.com><i>Referral Information</i></A><br>
</blockquote>
<p>

<h5 align=center>You can also contact the following support organizations:</h5><p>

<h5 align=center>The CFIDS Association of America at 800-44-CFIDS or <A HREF=mailto:cfids@vnet.net><i>cfids@vnet.net</i></A></h5><br>

<br><p>

<h5 align=center><IMG SRC = "../images/icons/eyes.gif"></h5>

<p>

<h2 align=center><i>Mission Statement</i></h2><p>

<br>
<blockquote>
The mission of the Worldwide Electronic CFIDS/ME Action Network will be to:<p>

<ol>
<li>campaign against bias, discrimination, and misinformation regarding CFIDS/M.E. wherever encountered: by employers; governments and their agencies; insurance providers; the scientific community; health professionals and organizations; or in the news media.<p>
 
<li> advocate on behalf of persons with CFIDS/M.E. with regard to:
<ul>
<li>   -greater awareness of the prevalence and severity of CFIDS/M.E.
<li>   -research into the etiology and treatment of the disease.
<li>   -financial and medical support for those afflicted with the disease.
<li>   -international coordination of information and resources.
<li>   -fair treatment by the insurance industry.
<li>   -hope for those isolated or impoverished by the disabilities that
      characterize this illness.
<li>   -an equal chance at diagnosis and treatment for all, whatever
      their nationality, age, gender, race, or income.
 </ul>
</ol>
<b>Together, WECAN.</b><p>
 
</blockquote>
