<PRE>    </PRE>Publications - fact sheets on aspects of caring, nursing booklet available<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>from Head Office, personal advice from Family Services, Family Support<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>Schemes and local contacts in various regions - details from Head Office.

<H4>Community Health Councils</H4>
<PRE>    </PRE>These Councils are a useful source of information about all health services<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>in your area, and can help if you are dissatisfied with the service you are<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>getting. In telephone book under town/district or ask your Social Services<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>Department.

<H4>Council for the Disabled</H4>
<PRE>    </PRE>Umbrella group for local organisations, can give advice on services and<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>policies in your area. In telephone book under town/district or ask your<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>Social Services Department.

<H4>Council for Voluntary Service</H4>
<PRE>    </PRE>Co-ordinating body for voluntary effort; sometimes able to provide<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>emergency help or advice. In telephone book under town/district or<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>ask your Social Services Department.

<H4>Crossroads Care Attendant Scheme</H4>
<PRE>    </PRE>Local schemes to give practical support by arranging help in homes<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>of families under stress. Contact Social Services or the Trust,<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>10 Regent Place, Rugby, Warwickshire CV21 2PN (01788 573653) to find<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>out if there is a scheme in your area.

<H4>Disability Alliance</H4>
<PRE>    </PRE>Provides excellent Disabilty Rights Handbook and a telephone rights<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>service - (0171-247-8776).<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>Universal House, Wentworth Street, London E1 7SA

<H4>Disabled Resettlement Office</H4>
<PRE>    </PRE>Gives information and guidance on sheltered and open employment for<BR>
<PRE>    </PRE>the disabled. In telephone under Employment, Dept. of.

