<p>
Sets out when and why psychiatrists prescribe major tranquillizers. This handbook also offers a list of the drugs and their brand names, their adverse effects, comparing and contrasting them. Also discusses informed consent to treatment and alternatives to tranquillizers, such as crisis centres or talking treatments.
<p>
MIND, 1993, 1-874690-09-X, pp64, £2.00
