Minor tranquillizers have been the most commonly prescribed drugs in the western world. This guide explains when and why minor tranquillizers are prescribed and their adverse effects. It also offers a list of the drugs and their brand names.
<p>
MIND, 1995, 1-874690-45-6, pp32, £2.00
