<h2><a name="indsls">Independent Schools</a></h2>
Information and advice on independent schools providing specialised teaching for children with Specific Learning Difficulties can be abtained from:<p>
<h4 align=center>Scottish Council for Independent Schools<br>Floor 2/1<br>11 Castle Street<br>Edinburgh EH2 3AH<p>Tel: 0131-220-2106</h4><br>
A booklet, <b>"Independent Schools Catering for Dyslexics"</b> can be obtained at a cost of £5.00 from:<p>
<h4 align=center>National ISIS<br>56 Buckingham Gate<br>London SW1E<p>Tel: 0171-630-8793/4</h4><br>
An updated list of specialist and mainstream schools, incuding maintained and independent, day and boarding schools, which have been accredited by professional consultants for teaching and care of dyslexic children, can be obtained from:<p>
<h4 align=center>Council for the Registration of Schools Teaching Dyslexic Pupils<br>9 Elgy Road<br>Gosforth<br>Newcastle upon Tyne NE3 4UU</h4><p><br>
<hr>
<h2><a name="funds">Funding</a></h2>
<h4 align=center>Students Awards Agency for Scotland<br>Gyleview House<br>3 Redheugh Rigg<br>Edinburgh EH12 9HH<p>Tel: 0130-244-5823 / 0131-556-8400</h4><br>
<h5 align=center>The Students Awards Agency processes all Student Grants in Scotland above HNC level and provides advice on available grants.</h5><br>
<h4 align=center>Scottish Council for Voluntary Organisation<br>18/19 Claremont Crescent<br>Edinburgh EH7 4QD<p>Tel: 0131-556-3882</h4><br>
<h5 align=center>National co-ordinating body for voluntary organisations in Scotland and produces on-going support for voluntary organisations.</h5><br>
