<h2><a name="sources">Further and Higher Education</a></h2>
<h3>Sources of Advice</h3>
A booklet entitled <b>"Access to Success"</b> provides information for any Student who requires additional support, advice or guidance in order to enjoy equal access to educational provision. A copy can be obtained from:<p>
<h4 align=center>The Scottish Higher Education Funding Council<br>Donaldson Lodge<br>97 Haymarket<br>Edinburgh EH12 5HD<p>Tel: 0131-313-6500</h4><br>
Assistance can also be obtained from:<p>
a) on higher education:<p>
<h4 align=center>Paul Brown<br>Co-ordinator for Higher Education Institutions<br>Ewing Annexe, Dundee University<br>Dundee DD1 4HN<p>Tel: 01382-345498</h4><br>
b) on further education:<p>
<h4 align=center>Scottish Further Education Unit<br>Jordanhill Campus<br>University of Strathclyde<br>Southbrae Drive, Glasgow G13 1PP<p>Tel: 0141-950-3149/3163</h4><br>
<h3>National Federation of Access Centres</h3>

<table border=1  cellpadding=4 cellspacing=1>
