<head>
<title>Paula's Poem</title>
</head>
<body background=../images/backgrounds/wtile3.gif>
<h1 align=center>A Poem from Paula</h1>
<hr>
<pre><b><h3>	     Walk With Us Awhile</h3>
	You laugh at us and mock us,
	you media and 'doctuhs'.
	You tell us it's all in our head,
	and we've no business staying in bed.
	You call us malingerers and liars;
	tho' before this illness we set the world on fire.

	There was no job we couldn't do;
	Our minds so quick and straight and true.
	To turn back time, reset the clock,
	our only dream, our only rock;
	Of hope and faith of healing power
	to turn us back to an earlier hour,
	Of strenth of body and clearness of mind,
	exhaustion no more, or pain unkind.

	We search and try for any cure,
	for this illness we can no longer endure.
	So stop your jokes, erase your smiles;
	unless you've walked with us awhile.
	'Cuz it's for sure you'll start to dread,
	the thought of following in our treads.

	Copyright 1996 Paula Frighetti

This poem can be reprinted provided the copyright information is included.
</pre></b>
