<head>
<title>Thanks from Phyllis</title>
</head>
<body background=../images/backgrounds/wtile3.gif>
<h2 align=center>A Thank you from Phyllis<br>
to all on alt.med.cfs</h2>
<hr>
        I sit here, brain in fog and body more than half asleep.
        I don't always understand what the posts to this board are
        about, so I often skip over many of them. Sometimes I say
        stupid things and get my references all mixed up. I get
        worse every winter, but with spring I seem to get stronger
        and my mind does clear.
<p>

        I've only recently found this place. It is hard for me to
        remember from day to day how to operate my computer to do
        anything more than read and reply to my e-mail. I'm glad
        I found this place.
<p>


        This DD has destroyed my life. My career is gone. My independance
        is gone. My income trashed. My self esteem steamrolled. My
        friends and social contacts are ancient history. I have sat
        home alone many times and cried in my dispair and loneliness
        with only my cats to wipe away my tears.
<p>

        This place is giving me back a feeling of being connected to
        the world. I don't feel so isolated anymore, and being
        housebound isn't so bad because every day I look forward to
        my box of e-mail. I feel that maybe someone out there does care
        if I were to fall off the face of the earth forever..simply
        because they can understand how alone and helpless I feel.
        I don't have to keep my chin up and be stoic every day. I can
        say that I hurt and someone will reply..I hear you..it's OK.
        I understand.
<p>

        Thanks for just being there..
<p>

        Phyllis G.  ..Victoria, B.C.
<hr>
<a href="personal.html"><img src="back.gif"></a>
</body>
</html>

