<body>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Research</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<H2>Current Research</H2>
<HR><A HREF="Concept.html">Concept of Stealth Viruses</A><P>Research is focused on the following areas:<DL><DD>1. Improving methods for detecting and characterizing stealth viral infections using both tissue culture, molecular, and serological techniques so as to determine the prevalence of simian cytomegalovirus derived stealth viruses in the general population.<DD><P>2. Sequencing stealth viruses isolated from a series of twelve severely ill patients.  <DD><P>3.  Associating stealth viral infection with specific neurological and non-neurological diseases.<DD><P>4.  Developing therapeutic agents to inhibit stealth viruses.</DL><P><HR>The following micrographs illustrate different aspects of stealth viral infection.<P><A HREF="yvirus1.gif"><img alt="" src=syvirus1.gif></A> Cytopathic effect (CPE) in human cells caused by a stealth virus isolated from a CFS patient.<P><A HREF="partial.gif"><img alt=""  src=spartial.gif></A> Electron micrograph of stealth viruses.  Note the incomplete nature (empty shells) of some of the viral particles.<P><A HREF="empty.gif"><img alt=""  src=sempty.gif></A> An incomplete stealth virus.<P><A HREF="full.gif"><img alt="" src=sfull.gif></A> A fully formed stealth virus.<P><A HREF="cluster.gif"><IMG SRC="scluster.gif"></A> <A HREF="dark.gif"><IMG SRC="sdark.gif"></A> Clusters of stealth viruses inside cells.<P>A <A HREF="babyxv.gif"><IMG ALT="" SRC=sbabyxv.gif></A>  B <A HREF="env.gif"><IMG ALT="" SRC=senv.gif></A>  C <A HREF="unenv.gif><IMG ALT="" SRC=sunenv.gif></A> Micrograph A shows a stealth virus-infected foamy cell.  Enveloped viral particles are present in the cytoplasm (B), and nascent, unenveloped viral particles are seen in the nucleus (C).<P><A HREF="pools.gif><img alt="" src=spools.gif></A> Electron micrograph of a vacuolated, "foamy cell."  Arrows on the left indicate lipid-filled vacuoles.  The amorphous grey mass indicated by the vertical arrow on the right is presumed to be a viral protein, the result of an unbalanced synthesis of viral components.<P><A HREF="brain.gif"><img alt="" src=sbrain.gif></A> Electron micrograph of a vacuolated glial cell seen in a 
<A NAME="biopsy">stereotactic</a> <A HREF="Viral_Infection.html#neural"> brain biopsy</A> from a patient with a stealth virus encephalopathy.  Small, dark, viral-like particles can be seen.  Note the adjacent empty and lipid-filled vacuoles in the lower right side of the cell.  The round body in the upper left is an axon surrounded by a myelin sheath.<HR>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="back.gif"></A><P>
</body>
