<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Stealth</TITLE></HEAD><body><CENTER><IMG BORDER=1 SRC="header.gif"></CENTER></A><body><P><HR>Welcome to the Stealth Virus Research Program at the USC Infectious Disease Laboratory. This Page is intended to provide information about a group of viruses that has previously gone unrecognized.  These viruses were initially identified in patients with chronic fatigue syndrome (CFS) and have since been isolated from patients with a wide variety of illnesses including severe encephalopathy, autism, and other complex neurological and non-neurological diseases.<P>We hope this Page will contribute to the knowledge of emerging viral diseases and be of interest to patients, physicians and researchers.<P><UL><B><P><A HREF="Research.html">Research</A><P><A HREF="Publications.html">Publications</A><P><A HREF="Patient_Information.html">Patient Information</A><P><A HREF="Questions.html">Questions and Comments</A><P><A HREF="Funding.html">Funding</A><P><a href="handout.html">Handout</a></UL></B><P>Special thanks go to Jim Tarleton, Tim Galaher, and Eric Havrilesky for equipment loan and technical support.  <HR>
