<body background=../images/backgrounds/map.gif>
<blockquote>
<b>WECAN<br></b>
Worldwide Electronic CFIDS/M.E. Action Network<br>
P.O. Box 805 ~Hockessin, DE 19707-0805<br>
Phone (610) 519-7403 
<p>
The Honorable Donna Shalala<br>
U.S. Department of Health and Human Services<br>
200 Independence Avenue, S.W.<br>
Washington, D.C. 20201
<p>
October 16, 1996<p>
<b>SUBJECT:  DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES 
                    SUBMISSION OF NOMINEE FOR CFSCC PATIENT 
REPRESENTATIVE</b>
<p>

Dear Secretary Shalala,
<p>
We understand that there are several positions that will become 
available on the Chronic  Fatigue Syndrome Coordinating Committee for 
the next four year term.
<p>
The 102 members of WECAN, which stands for Worldwide Electronic 
CFIDS/M.E. Action Network, respectfully request that our nominee be 
given serious consideration for the position of Patient Representative 
on the CFS Coordinating Committee.  Please refer to
the enclosed, comprehensive description of WECAN, which outlines the 
nature and scope of our organization.
<p>

The WECAN member, that we proudly endorse and submit for your 
consideration, is Mary M. Schweitzer, Co-founder of WECAN in May 1996, 
presently serving as Secretary, Steering Committee, Insurance and Media Committees. 
 Ms. Schweitzer has been a PWC (Person with Chronic
Fatigue Immune Dysfunction Syndrome) for six years.  We are also 
submitting our alternate nominee John Friedlich,  WECAN Member and a PWC.
Mr. Friedlich has also served as official special contributor on the Prodigy Medical 
Support CFS bulletin board.
<p>
Enclosed, please find the Curriculum Vita and Letter of Interest for our 
nominee, Mary M. Schweitzer, which most effectively demonstrates her 
capabilities, experience and strong desire to serve on such an important 
committee as the Patient Representative
for the CFSCC.  Also, please find the Biographical Information and Letter of Interest 
for John Friedlich, our alternate nominee.
<p>

Page 2<br>
WECAN
<p>
October 16, 1996
<p>

WECAN, resolutely request, that you consider the immediate replacement 
of Orvalene Prewitt, the National Chronic Fatigue Syndrome and 
Fibromyalgia Association Patient Representative, currently serving on 
the CFS(I)CC.  Thankfully, Ms. Prewitt does not personally suffer from Chronic Fatigue Immune Dysfunction Syndrome.  It is 
the conviction, by many in the PWC community, that if the Patient 
Representatives were a PWC themselves, they would be more understanding 
and responsive to the needs of all PWCs.
<p>
The second primary complaint with Ms. Prewitts representation, is her 
flagrant inadequacy in regards to communicating with the CFIDS/M.E. 
community.  This is most distressing to all of us who have repeatedly 
tried to communicate with her.  It is imperative that we have a representative voice who will actively pursue open 
and honest communication between themselves, as a member of the CFS 
Coordinating Committee, and all PWCs nationwide through their 
respective CFIDS/M.E. Organizations.
<p>

WECAN joins with the other CFIDS/M.E. Organizations, RESCIND and the 
CAA, in support of their slate of nominees.  We do, of course, support 
and endorse our nominee, Ms. Schweitzer, as our primary nominee and John 
Friedlich as alternate.  We also join with
 all of the CFIDS/M.E. Organizations, in appealing to you for the 
immediate removal of Orvalene Prewitt from the CFS(I)CC.
<p>
 



The invaluable work that has been, and will continue to be accomplished by the CFS(I)CC is 
tremendously important to the thousands, if not millions, of the 
children, women and men who suffer from this most serious and 
debilitating illness.  We want even a small part our former 
lives back!
<p>
Thank you for your tenacious spirit, understanding and belief in the 
tremendous suffering of all PWCs and the serious need for ongoing 
research into etiology, treatment and education.  We also thank you for 
your serious consideration of our nominee for
this most important position.
<p>
 Please contact me if I can be of any assistance regarding WECANs nomination to the
 CFSCC.

<p>
Together, WECAN
<p>
Sincerely,
<p>


Sandra R. Ponce
WECAN - Chairperson,  ICC (Interagency Coordinating Committee) 


<p>


Page 3<br>
WECAN
<p>
October 16, 1996
<p>

(WECAN - Contact Person)<br>
Sandra R. Ponce
<p>


