A new edition of a widely-used handbook which provudes a step-by-step guide for lawyers on the procedures of the Court of Protection.
<p>
Oyez Longma, 1988, 0-85121-831-8, pp147, £26.00
<hr>
<B>Mental Health Act 1983 - An Outline Guide</B>
<p>
A clear and concise guide to the ACT
<p>
MIND, 50p, £4.50 per 10, £40.00 per 100, £320.00 per 1000
<hr>
<B>Mental Health Act Manual:</B> <B><I>Richard Jones</I></B>
<p>
It is essential for those working in the mental health field to understand the Mental Health Act 1983, the implications of cases arising from it and subsequent changes in legislation. The "Mental Health Act Manual" provides this material for all those involved in the care of the mentally disordered. This text incorporates changes made to the law by recent Acts such as the NHS and Community Care Act 1990, Childrens Act 1989 and the Courts and Legal Services Act 1990. This fourth edition includes the revised Code of Practice Notes issued by the Mental Health Act Commission and a number of recently published circulars on the Criminal Procedure Act 1991 and the recall of restricted patients. A valuable book for all those working in menatl health law.
<p>
Sweet & Maxwell, 1994, 4th edition, 0-421-51120-6, pp500, £32.00
<hr>
<B>Mental Health Handbook (Law) - A Guide to the Law Affecting Children and Young People</B>
<p>
This fully revised second edition is a unique guide for all those advising, supporting and working with children and young people who are seen as having mental health problems. Includes a succinct summary of the law in the four systems in which such children and young people may find themselves: mental health, education, child care and juvenile justice.
<p>
Children's Legal Centre, 1994, 0-946109-20-6, £9.99, Please quote code "LAW" when ordering.
<hr>
