<a name="carol"></a>
<H4> Community</H4>

<b> There's "Can't in the Community",
 There's "Critical of me in the Community",
 There's "Cruel in the Community",
 There's them that are ignoring me,
 There's even some avoiding me,
 There's crying but not heeding me,
 There's words that cannot access me,
 There's only half the therapy!
 There's nobody available!

 There's homelessness where ones told to be,
 "Bloody working you lazy git", but,
 There's no jobs for me and that was the first casualty.
 There's "Equality", but that doesn't apply to "Disability".
 There's friendship and there's family -
 But I mustn't tell the family,
 And the friends are "Mental" same as me -
 The hospital's our Community,
 And they're "Closing the Community".

 There's a "Chemical Straight-jacket"
 That means that we,
 Sit silently, lonely, passively.
 Needing someone to talk to me,
 But what "Care in the Community"!
 They're closing the community,
 And putting us out on the street,
 Talk of care that is not there
 In us and self deceit.

                      Carol Batton 24th October 1990



 I've a fear of medication
 My fear becomes consternation,
 They may medicate my consternation -
 It was only fear of medication.

                      Carol Batton 5th December 1990




<h4> Tranquilized</h4>

 I used to chat to strangers,
 Natter on so incoherent,
 And neither did I notice,
 That they could not understand me.

 Now that they have slowed me,
 With medication,
 Makes me lonely,
 So they give me top rank nurses
     To talk to,
            'Cos I'm lonely.

                       Carol Batton 13-01-94




<h4> The Parker Pen</h4>

 It's not the medication,
 "The illness is at fault".
 You can quote me,
 But not the patient;
 (She's psychotic),
    (And nowadays neurotic),

 About Lithium, the "Wonder drug!",
 Quote the medication journal -
 She's just upset she's "normal",
 She's "well", but being mad,
 She can't understand, she's not sad;
     Just no longer happy.

 A decade of wanting death? -
 That I can't record as true,
 (Because it's not been noted before).
 It's her illness, (not the Lithium),
     I'm sure,

 And how many peoples' illness changes
 From Manic to - Depressed, "Cured",
 By Lithium?.....
 Looking so much less distressed,
 Depressed?
      We note she's well.

 I always felt such "Fear",
 Of the psychiatrist and his power...
 I was mistaken,
 Twas not fear -
 Powerless anger, at tears, and
 At lies,....
 For he has his Prescription Pen,
      And my Parker writes Poetry.

                         Carol Batton 14-10-92




<h4> Apologia</h4>

 I smoke
 My thumb
 I use the same one,
 Which can nearly always
 Be done,
 And it is not a fire risk,
 Or cancer risk.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 It's free
 You see
 And a harmlessly produced
 Commodity,
 With few side effects.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 It's lasted me years
 It's as good as new,
 And I only once misplaced it;
 A train door encased it,
 And it wasn't on line for a time.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 It's easily done
 And comforting fun
 No danger to health
 Or wealth
 And I can still run.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 And I've never seen a sign
 "No Sucking Allowed"
 Because it's benign
 And not loud
 (And not expected).

 I smoke
 My thumb
 I'm not being funny
 It's literally nice,
 Though I've tried to give
 Up twice.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 Though it comes
 Unwrapped,
 And I can't put it back,
 In a packet,
 I can park it
 In my jacket pocket.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 It's very handy
 And I do it in bed
 And though I fall asleep
 With it,
 I do not "wake up" dead.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 It's just the right size
 I don't smoke cigarettes
 Aren't I wise?

 I smoke
 My thumb
 If I can't give up that,
 It's a good thing
 I've never tried
 Hard drugs
 Or fags!

 I smoke
 My thumb
 It helps me to sleep
 Those "sleeping tablets"
 Aren't good for sleep -
 Like my thumb.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 For seconds, or hours
 I don't have to book
 Or light it,
 And it has no wires.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 'Til it's been know to
 Get numb.
 But it's a safety device
 To keep it nice.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 No it's not
 An idiom
 By now
 You will realize
 I do smoke my thumb.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 Not easily done
 'Cos it's not the done thing
 But what the hell
 I'm explaining to you
 As best as I can.

 I smoke
 My thumb
 Which calms me well
 Though people remark
 On my thumb
 Can't they tell
 That they should be
 Doing it as well?

          Carol Batton 6th July 1991




<h4> Nearly Never</h4>

 Forever we're relinquishing,
 The present, to the past,
 Near to never finishing,
 What we failed to start.

 Nearly never made it,
 Nearly never went,
 Nearly never compromised,
 And spent the time in hate.

 Nearly never sang, and though,
 There was no tune,
 I spoke,
 Nearly never visualized, this far.

 Never really found myself,
 When the times were lost,
 Never really liked to laugh,
 I found my Truths in sobs.

 Nearly never cried one day,
 When I needed tears;
 Really nearly cried to think
 I couldn't Smile;
 Never very far from fear,
 Life nearly Robs.

 Never going far from home,
 Until I roam, too far, to return.
 Never singing, 'til trying a tune,
 I find that I am off the scale.

 Never playing, 'cos it's not a game,
 And if it is, well what's the point?
 Never silent, I've so much to say,
 Until they say, have silence pills.

 Nearer to the Dawn at night,
 Further from the light,
 At dusk.
 Near to gone and written it,
 (Didn't fail to start),
 Vague impressions of the often,
 Too much trying heart.

                         Carol Batton 2-4-94




 I say what my emotions are
 That's all I do with time....
 I'm feeling chuffed that really though,
 I do a thing sublime;
 I note the things I see in life -
 And I do it all in rhyme.
 (Usually more profound than this),
 Does it need an extra line?

                          Carol Batton









<img src="../images/logos/mouse.gif" hspace=5><a href="work.html#content"> Back to Contributor's List</a></b>

</pre>
