<b>Community Organizational Experience (as a youth):</b>
<ul>
<li>      1968-69, as an Oberlin College undergraduate, organized and taught
 a college-credit course in early childhood education while helping run
 a day-care center for poverty-level children
<li>      1970-73, participated in the early Womens Movement; worked with
 women on welfare to help alleviate their problems; worked with battered
 women; member of a Hispanic community organization and helped with a
 local Hispanic clinic.
</ul>

<b>Community Organizational Experience (as a parent and citizen):<br></b>
(All in my home state of Delaware):
<ul>
<li> CHADD (children and adults with ADD) and other learning disability
 advocacy activities (my son has ADD and my daughter and husband are
 both dyslexic);
<li>GHADA (Greater Hockessin Area Development Association)
 a community association;
<li>A.I. duPont High School Sports Boosters;
<li> Vice President, Ladies Auxiliary, Newark American Little League;
<li> various school parent-teacher organizations.
</ul>

