<head><title>The Fuzzboy Page</title></head>
<body>
<img align=left hspace=20 vspace=5 width=210 height=188 src="fuzzboy-logo.gif"><br>
<br>
<h1><center>The Fuzzboy Page</center></h1>
<br clear=all>
<p><hr><p>
Fuzzboy is the ambient/techno/industrial musical group that consists mainly of
<a href="../home/danfuzz/">Danfuzz</a> and his equipment.
One Fuzzboy song (``Sacrificial Lamb'') currently appears on the
<tt>rec.music.industrial</tt> compilation
CD <a href="http://isl-garnet.uah.edu/claassen/RMI/rmi2.html"><cite>Mind/Body
#2</cite></a>, and more songs are available
on <a href="http://isl-garnet.uah.edu/claassen/RMI/rmic.html"><cite>Children 
of RMI</cite></a>--a follow-on CD laid out as 4 EPs 
from different groups. The Fuzzboy part is entitled <cite>Punch
Tone Generator</cite>.

<h3>Have A Listen</h3>
Sorry, but the bog-standard <tt>.au</tt> format makes music samples
sound awful. Until there's a free MPEG-audio compressor, I'm using
AIFF.

<ul>
<li><a href="sacrificial.aiff">excerpt from Sacrificial Lamb</a> (22kHz AIFF, 1228k, about 1 minute)
</ul>

All audio samples on this site are copyright &copy; 1994, Dan Bornstein. All
rights reserved. Like I had to tell you, okay?

<h3>Ordering Information</h3>
To order, send email to 
<a href="mailto:atomrec@primus.com">atomrec@primus.com</a>. The double
CD <cite>Mind/Body #2</cite> is $10 plus shipping and <cite>Children</cite> 
is $6.50 plus shipping. You might mention where you heard about
the <cite>Mind/Body</cite> project.

<p>
Also, check out <a href="http://isl-garnet.uah.edu/claassen/RMI/">the
<tt>rec.music.industrial</tt> CD Home Page</a>, which has further
updates and information on other <cite>Mind/Body</cite> activities.

<h3>Fuzzboy's Influences Include</h3>
<ul>
<li>Aphex Twin
<li>Clock DVA
<li>Coil
<li>Einst&uuml;rzende Neubauten
<li>Front 242
<li>Legendary Pink Dots
<li>William Orbit
<li>Orbital
<li>Skinny Puppy
<li>John Zorn
</ul>

<p><hr><address><a href="../home/danfuzz/">-dan</a></address>
</body>



